      "  this reads as more dimensional than a flat straight-on shot.",
      "  Straight-on or top-down is fine when the product calls for it.",
      "- The product is sharp and in focus from edge to edge. Standard",
      "  product-photography depth of field at f/8 — the entire product is",
      "  crisp; only the backdrop softens.",
      "",
      "LIGHTING:",
      "- Soft, even, color-accurate studio light. Imagine: a large softbox",
      "  key light positioned upper-left at 45°, a white bounce card on the",
      "  right filling shadows, an optional rim light from behind for edge",
      "  separation. The lighting is FLATTERING but TRUTHFUL — it makes the",
      "  product look its best without distorting its real colors.",
      "- Highlights are soft and rolling, not blown out. Shadows are gentle",
      "  and detail-preserving, not crushed. The product's surface texture",
      "  reads clearly — matte stays matte, glossy reflects believably,",
      "  metallic shows real specular highlights.",
      "- The product's printed colors come through bit-identically. The",
      "  yellow/red of a foil package stays the same yellow/red — no",
      "  white-balance shift, no warming, no cooling, no saturation boost.",
      "",
      "CONTACT SHADOW:",
      "- A subtle, soft contact shadow grounds the product on the backdrop.",
      "  The shadow is darkest directly beneath the product (where it",
