      "- On the PRODUCT: droplets vary in size (~0.3–2% of canvas width each), some forming small rivulets running down the bottle's surface, some clinging in clusters around the cap, label edges, and lower curves. Each droplet has subtle real-light catchlight + a tiny shadow + visible meniscus where it meets the surface.",
      "- IN THE AIR around the product: 10–20 floating water droplets and liquid splashes suspended mid-flight, with realistic motion blur on a few and crisp focus on others — creating a frozen-moment dynamism.",
      "- ABSOLUTE RULE: droplets NEVER cover or obscure the product's brand mark, primary label text, or any printed graphic. They cluster on the cap, on the lower portion of the bottle, on the sides — but the brand and product name stay fully readable.",
      "- The water reads as a real photographic shot taken with high-shutter-speed flash photography — not as a digital sparkle effect, not as bubbles.",
      "",
      "INGREDIENT PROPS AT THE BASE:",
