      "  Step 2: The BACKGROUND is a SOFT PASTEL TINT of that accent — very pale pink for a pink product, very pale blue for a blue product, soft cream for a cream/tan product, soft gray for a black/gray product, soft mint for a green product. The pastel is LIGHT (~10–18% saturation), bright, breathable. Subtle gradient — slightly brighter at the center behind the product, slightly deeper at the edges. NEVER pure white, NEVER saturated, NEVER dark.",
      "  Step 3: The MAIN HEADLINE color is a TWO-COLOR VERTICAL GRADIENT — top half in a warm metallic / champagne / gold tone (or deep tone of the accent), bottom half fading into a slightly different tone of the same family (e.g. gold at top fading into rose-gold at bottom; deep brown at top fading into warm caramel; deep navy at top fading into soft teal). The gradient is SMOOTH and SUBTLE — not flat, but not high-contrast either. This is the defining typographic move.",
