      "  Step 2: The PRIMARY ACCENT color (used for the top watercolor brushstroke banner, the watercolor cloud callouts, the eucalyptus illustrated leaves, the curved arrows, the sparkle stars) is a SOFT SAGE GREEN or DUSTY TEAL — desaturated, watercolor-rendered, with visible paint texture and translucent edge bleeds. This is the wellness/herbal signature color.",
      "  Step 3: The SECONDARY ACCENT color appears in supporting illustrations — soft honey-amber for oil-drop illustrations, soft lavender for moon/sleep illustrations, soft terracotta for brain/grounding illustrations, soft butter-yellow for sun/energy illustrations. Each illustration uses ITS OWN small palette drawn from the symbolic theme, but ALL pulled from a warm vintage palette — never bright or neon.",
